#. <section class="sutta" id="sn22.22"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.22:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.22:0.2"
msgid "3. Bhāravagga"
msgstr "3. The Burden"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn22.22:0.3"
msgid "22. Bhārasutta"
msgstr "22. The Burden"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.22:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ … tatra kho …"
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn22.22:1.2"
msgid ""
"“bhārañca vo, bhikkhave, desessāmi bhārahārañca bhārādānañca "
"bhāranikkhepanañca."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, I will teach you the burden, the bearer of the burden, the "
"picking up of the burden, and the putting down of the burden."

msgctxt "sn22.22:1.3"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha."
msgstr "Listen …"

msgctxt "sn22.22:1.4"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, bhāro?"
msgstr "And what is the burden?"

msgctxt "sn22.22:1.5"
msgid "Pañcupādānakkhandhā tissa vacanīyaṃ."
msgstr "The five grasping aggregates, it should be said."

msgctxt "sn22.22:1.6"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "sn22.22:1.7"
msgid ""
"Rūpupādānakkhandho, vedanupādānakkhandho, saññupādānakkhandho, "
"saṅkhārupādānakkhandho, viññāṇupādānakkhandho;"
msgstr ""
"The grasping aggregates of form, feeling, perception, choices, and "
"consciousness."

msgctxt "sn22.22:1.8"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhāro."
msgstr "This is called the burden."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.22:2.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, bhārahāro?"
msgstr "And who is the bearer of the burden?"

msgctxt "sn22.22:2.2"
msgid "Puggalo tissa vacanīyaṃ."
msgstr "The person, it should be said;"

msgctxt "sn22.22:2.3"
msgid "Yvāyaṃ āyasmā evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto;"
msgstr "the venerable of such and such name and clan."

msgctxt "sn22.22:2.4"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhārahāro."
msgstr "This is called the bearer of the burden."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.26"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.22:3.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, bhārādānaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the picking up of the burden?"

# As usual, I prefer to translate tatra tatra and related idioms as distributive.
#. VAR: ponobhavikā → ponobbhavikā (s1-3, km, mr)
#. VAR: nandīrāgasahagatā → nandirāgasahagatā (sabbattha)
msgctxt "sn22.22:3.2"
msgid ""
"Yāyaṃ taṇhā ponobhavikā nandīrāgasahagatā tatratatrābhinandinī, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"It’s the craving that leads to future rebirth, mixed up with relishing and "
"greed, taking pleasure in various different realms. That is,"

msgctxt "sn22.22:3.3"
msgid "kāmataṇhā, bhavataṇhā, vibhavataṇhā."
msgstr ""
"craving for sensual pleasures, craving to continue existence, and craving to "
"end existence."

msgctxt "sn22.22:3.4"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhārādānaṃ."
msgstr "This is called the picking up of the burden."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.22:4.1"
msgid "Katamañca, bhikkhave, bhāranikkhepanaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the putting down of the burden?"

msgctxt "sn22.22:4.2"
msgid ""
"Yo tassāyeva taṇhāya asesavirāganirodho cāgo paṭinissaggo mutti anālayo."
msgstr ""
"It’s the fading away and cessation of that very same craving with nothing "
"left over; giving it away, letting it go, releasing it, and not clinging to "
"it."

msgctxt "sn22.22:4.3"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhāranikkhepanan”ti."
msgstr "This is called the putting down of the burden.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.22:5.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

#. VAR: vatvāna → vatvā (bj)
msgctxt "sn22.22:5.2"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.22:6.1"
msgid "“Bhārā have pañcakkhandhā,"
msgstr "“The five aggregates are indeed burdens,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn22.22:6.2"
msgid "bhārahāro ca puggalo;"
msgstr "and the person is the bearer of the burden."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn22.22:6.3"
msgid "Bhārādānaṃ dukhaṃ loke,"
msgstr "Picking up the burden is suffering in the world,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn22.22:6.4"
msgid "bhāranikkhepanaṃ sukhaṃ."
msgstr "and putting the burden down is happiness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.22:7.1"
msgid "Nikkhipitvā garuṃ bhāraṃ,"
msgstr "When the heavy burden is put down"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn22.22:7.2"
msgid "aññaṃ bhāraṃ anādiya;"
msgstr "without picking up another,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: taṇhamabbuyha → taṇhaṃ abbuyha (bj, s1-3) | taṇhamabbhuyha (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn22.22:7.3"
msgid "Samūlaṃ taṇhamabbuyha,"
msgstr "and craving’s pulled out from the root,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn22.22:7.4"
msgid "nicchāto parinibbuto”ti."
msgstr "you’re hungerless, extinguished.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.22:7.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
